### PHP File Read

PHP offers multiple ways to read file contents.

### Reading Methods

| Method | Description | Use Case |
|--------|-------------|----------|
| `fread()` | Read raw bytes | Binary files |
| `fgets()` | Read one line | Text files (line by line) |
| `fgetc()` | Read one character | Character-by-character |
| `file()` | Read into array (by lines) | Small files, array processing |
| `file_get_contents()` | Read entire file into string | Small files, API responses |
| `readfile()` | Read and output directly | Streaming to browser |

### Examples

```php
<?php
// Read entire file
$content = file_get_contents("test.txt");
echo $content;

// Read into array (one line per element)
$lines = file("test.txt");
foreach ($lines as $line_num => $line) {
    echo "Line $line_num: " . htmlspecialchars($line) . "<br>";
}

// Read with fread
$file = fopen("test.txt", "r");
$content = fread($file, filesize("test.txt"));
fclose($file);

// Read line by line
$file = fopen("test.txt", "r");
while (!feof($file)) {
    $line = fgets($file);
    echo $line . "<br>";
}
fclose($file);
?>
```

> **Key Point:** `file_get_contents()` is the simplest way to read an entire file into a string, but use `fgets()` for large files to avoid memory issues.
